Here's how to handle each scenario in MSTest:

## 1. Windows-only (Registry access)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("WindowsOnly")]
public void ReadRegistryKey_ReturnsExpectedValue()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows.");
        return;
    }
    // ... test logic
}
```

Or create a reusable attribute (MSTest v3+):

```csharp
[AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Method)]
public class WindowsOnlyTestMethodAttribute : TestMethodAttribute
{
    public override TestResult[] Execute(ITestMethod testMethod)
    {
        if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
            return [new TestResult { Outcome = UnitTestOutcome.Inconclusive,
                TestFailureException = new AssertInconclusiveException("Windows only") }];
        return base.Execute(testMethod);
    }
}
```

## 2. Skip in CI (requires GPU)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void RenderFrame_ProducesOutput()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") is not null)
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU.");
        return;
    }
    // ... test logic
}
```

Then in CI, you can also **filter** at the command line:

```bash
dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"
```

## 3. Flaky external API — Retry

MSTest v3+ has a built-in `[Retry]` attribute:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // retries up to 3 times on failure
public void GetWeather_ReturnsValidForecast()
{
    var result = _weatherClient.GetForecast("Seattle");
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

## 4. Cleanup even on failure — `[TestCleanup]`

`[TestCleanup]` runs **regardless** of test outcome (pass, fail, or exception):

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string _tempFile = null!;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void ProcessFile_WritesExpectedContent()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "data");
        var result = MyProcessor.Process(_tempFile);
        Assert.AreEqual("expected", result);
    }

    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }
}
```

---

**Summary of patterns:**

| Scenario | Approach |
|----------|----------|
| OS-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` or custom `TestMethodAttribute` |
| Skip in CI | Env-var check + `Assert.Inconclusive()`, or `--filter` |
| Flaky/retry | `[Retry(N)]` (MSTest v3+) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` method |
